modules.description: Lists directory contents with file metadata, opens files with specified flags and permissions, and manages file descriptors. Provides low-level file operations such as reading, seeking, and closing. Works with file descriptors, open flags, and seek commands to interact with the file system.

Provides functions for parsing FTP server responses, extracting status codes, and handling directory listings. Works with strings, lists, and custom record types representing FTP commands and replies. Used to implement command-line FTP clients that process server interactions and file metadata.

Provides functions to list directory contents, open, read, seek, and close files over FTP. Operates with file descriptors, open flags, and seek commands to manage file operations. Enables retrieval of file statistics and controlled data reading from remote servers.
